<item>
            <title>[LU-18038] llog improvement- removing dt_record_write(tail) for every record adding</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18038</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;llog_osd_write_rec(...LLOG_NEXT_IDX..) has 3 operation for llog header modification&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dt_record_write(main header)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dt_record_write(part of bitmap 1 byte)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;dt_record_write(tail)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The last&#160;dt_record_write() could be removed with a changing llog_header format, if tail moves to a main header.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
